        <abstract> 
<p>Stupefied by CD’s trouble and kindness. All he wanted for Belfast meeting was assurance that mention of published work on <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi>, etc., in <hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, etc., would not interfere with CD’s book.</p>  
<p>Would like his <hi rend="italic">Nepenthes</hi> results to go to CD or to Royal Society, but prefers CD take them.</p>  
<p><hi rend="italic">Cephalotus</hi> very puzzling.</p>  
<p>Peas and cabbage grow twice as fast after two days’ immersion in <hi rend="italic">Nepenthes</hi> as when placed in distilled water, but four days’ immersion seems to kill them.</p>  
<p>Has a splendid Australian <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi> twice as big as <hi rend="italic">D. rotundifolia</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
